[Student "S"]
{With your 12 point hand you need to force to game. It would also be nice to find out if partner has a 4-card \H suit. Since you have East's \S suit stopped, you first bid a lebensohl 2NT.

Partner says 3\C.  

NOW you cue-bid 3\S. This is Stayman, but with a \S stopper, (SLOW SHOWS). Partner says 3NT and you pass.

}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:KQ8.AJ5.T6.KQJ94 AT5.84.K85432.A7 J964.KQ73.AQ9.T3 732.T962.J7.8652"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1NT 2D 2NT pass 3C pass 3D pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c58a5666f1e1cddcd0fb85bc488831e7806be2d74b04a9f5b726c60fab709c4e"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/lebensohl"]
[Student "S"]
{Partner's 2NT bid requests that you bid 3\C, so you do.

He next says 3\D.  

Partner has just described a hand with which he wants to play in game, which has at least one 4-card Major suit, and has \Ds stopped. He wants you to pick the game.

With no 4-card Major of your own, you pick 3NT.}

